<DocsLayout title="Dashboard" section="Dashboard & Reports">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    The <strong>Live Dashboard</strong> gives you a bird's eye view of your operations.
    Monitor key performance indicators and stay updated on work orders, operational metrics,
    and user activities in real-time.
  </p>
  <p>
    Dashboards bring all important information into one place, making it easy to track and act.
    This helps boost productivity, improve customer satisfaction, and increase profitability.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <p>The <strong>Home</strong> page is your dashboard â€” it's the default landing page.</p>

  <h2>Dashboard Sections</h2>

  <h3>Work Orders</h3>
  <img src="/images/dashboard-reports/dashboard_02.webp" alt="Work Orders Dashboard" />
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Today's:</strong> Work orders dispatched for the current day</li>
    <li><strong>Unassigned:</strong> Work orders not yet assigned to any technician</li>
    <li><strong>Recurrence:</strong> Recurring work orders that repeat on a schedule</li>
    <li><strong>Outdated:</strong> Past work orders where the technician hasn't filled in time or marked complete</li>
    <li><strong>All Open:</strong> Comprehensive view of all pending work orders</li>
    <li><strong>Completed:</strong> Work orders marked complete, ready for invoicing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Operational Metrics</h3>
  <img src="/images/dashboard-reports/dashboard_01.webp" alt="Operational Metrics" />
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Schedules:</strong> Summary of "In Progress" and "Completed" visits. Identifies discrepancies between Actual and Scheduled Hours</li>
    <li><strong>Estimates:</strong> Quick view of "Approved" and "Pending" estimate totals</li>
    <li><strong>Closed Orders:</strong> Trend graph of closed work orders for the past 24 months</li>
    <li><strong>Days Off:</strong> View upcoming days off and add new ones</li>
    <li><strong>Service Provider Status:</strong> Real-time technician status with 15-day history</li>
    <li><strong>Service Requests:</strong> Customer requests submitted through your website</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>User Activities</h3>
  <img src="/images/dashboard-reports/dashboard_03.webp" alt="User Activities" />
  <p>
    Monitor technician activities throughout the day. As tasks are completed, notifications
    appear in the User Activities list. Click an activity to open the related work order,
    or click the map icon to view the location where the task was performed.
  </p>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The dashboard <strong>automatically updates</strong> as work orders change status</li>
    <li>Only <strong>Administrators</strong> have access to the dashboard</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Monitor the dashboard continuously</strong> to catch important updates and act quickly.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Use the tiles</strong> to navigate directly to tasks that need attention.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Check the Outdated section</strong> daily to ensure no work orders fall through the cracks.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
